KW  - Venture capitalists
KW  - Decision aids
KW  - Cognitive feedback
AB  - This article proposes that research into decision aids can improve venture capitalists' (VCs) decision process and decision accuracy and speed up the acquisition of expertise. After reviewing research into the accuracy of decision aids such as bootstrapping models and the use of these models in cognitive learning, we propose that theory on the use and performance of decision aids can have important implications on how VCs gain expertise in predicting new venture performance. This discussion leads to a proposed research agenda.
